te_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Venki_Ramakrishnan_Home_Page_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Venkatraman_Ramakrishnan#cite_note-Venki_Ramakrishnan_Home_Page-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Upon the retirement of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Nurse\" title=\"Paul Nurse\">Paul Nurse<\/a>, Ramakrishnan will take up the post of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/President_of_the_Royal_Society\" title=\"President of the Royal Society\" class=\"mw-redirect\">President of the Royal Society<\/a> on November 30 2015.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Venkatraman_Ramakrishnan#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> In 2009 he shared the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a> with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Thomas_A._Steitz\" title=\"Thomas A. Steitz\">Thomas A. Steitz<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ada_E._Yonath\" title=\"Ada E. Yonath\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Ada E. Yonath<\/a>, \"for studies of the structure and function of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ribosome\" title=\"Ribosome\">ribosome<\/a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Venkatraman_Ramakrishnan#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Venkatraman Ramakrishnan","place_of_birth":"Chidambaram ,  Tamil Nadu , India","place_of_death":null,"text":"Venkatraman Ramakrishnan ,  born in India , Chemistry, 2009","year":2009.0}